In [[Ruby]], everything is an object, right? So let's create some!

minit.rb:
<pre class="sh_ruby">
class Minit

    def initialize()
        @barf = "blah"
    end

    def barf()
        puts @barf
    end
end
</pre>

new.rb:
<pre class="sh_ruby">
require "minit"

yo = Minit.new

yo.barf
</pre>

Runit:
<pre class="sh_sh">
# ruby new.rb
blah
</pre>

Nice and simple. Now let's try modifying that object we create.

minit.rb:
<pre class="sh_ruby">
class Minit

    @barf = "yo"

    def initialize()
        @barf = "blah"
    end

    def setme(newval)
        @barf = newval
    end

    def barf()
        puts @barf
    end
end
</pre>

new.rb:
<pre class="sh_ruby">
require "minit"
yo = Minit.new
yo.setme("yoyoyo")
yo.barf
</pre>

Yes, yoyoyo!

